### `lc help` (alias: `lchelp`) - List All Commands
Show a summary of all available `lc` commands.

**Action:** Print the following help text:

```
LiveComment Commands (aliases in parentheses):

  lc                  LiveComment current file - add structured comment blocks
  lc file [<path>]    LiveComment a specific file                          (lcfile)
  lc all              LiveComment all files in the project                 (lcall)
  lc find <keyword>   Find code sections by keyword (case-insensitive)    (lcfind)
  lc auto on/off      Auto-wrap new code in livecomment blocks            (lcauto)
  lc reload           Reload rules from ~/.cursor/rules/                  (lcreload)
  lc install          Install livecomment rule to global ~/.cursor/rules/ (lcinstall)
  lc help             Show this help message                              (lchelp)
```

### `lc install` (alias: `lcinstall`) - Install to Global Cursor Rules
Install the livecomment cursor rule to the global `~/.cursor/rules/` directory so it is available in all projects.

**Action:**
1. Detect OS and resolve the global rules directory:
   - **Linux**: `~/.cursor/rules/`
   - **Mac**: `~/.cursor/rules/`
   - **Windows**: `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\rules\`
2. Create the directory if it doesn't exist
3. Copy this project's `.cursor/rules/livecomment.mdc` to the global rules directory

**Commands:**

Linux / Mac:
```bash
mkdir -p ~/.cursor/rules && cp "<project_root>/.cursor/rules/livecomment.mdc" ~/.cursor/rules/livecomment.mdc
```

Windows (PowerShell):
```powershell
$dir = "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\rules"; if (!(Test-Path $dir)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $dir -Force }; Copy-Item "<project_root>\.cursor\rules\livecomment.mdc" "$dir\livecomment.mdc" -Force
```

Windows (cmd):
```cmd
if not exist "%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\rules" mkdir "%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\rules" & copy "<project_root>\.cursor\rules\livecomment.mdc" "%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\rules\livecomment.mdc"
```

